  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Age-related change of femur is not well-known. The investigators investigated the
      longitudinal changes of femur.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Recently, bisphosphonate-related atypical fracture of femur (AFF) is paid attention in
      clinicians. Almost all AFFs were occurred in thicker cortical thickness. But age-related
      change of femur is not well-known.

      The main objective of this study is to reveal the age-related change of femur.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
